Naming Conventions
Java is a case-sensitive language.

UpperCamelCase - classes
lowerCamelCase - methods and variables
SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE - constants
Snake_Case
snake_case
kebap-case 

Names can start with letters, $ or _ 
keywords can't be used while naming.

